                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13685.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Carothers</persName> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guadalupe</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-03T18:00:00-06:41">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 3, 1914, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>General Gutiérrez has authorized me to say that immediately upon taking oath as
                    Provisional President he will issue a proclamation conceding the request of the
                    Department regarding the evacuation of Vera Cruz. General Villa has authorized
                    me to say that he will support with his sword the proclamation of the President.
                    They both expressed the hope that when these assurances shall have been
                    fulfilled the Government of the United States will not further delay the
                    evacuation. General Gutiérrez informed me that the spirit of the Convention was
                    that, taking into consideration the extraordinary circumstances under which Vera
                    Cruz was occupied, those who served the Americans should be pardoned.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carothers</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
